ipswich.org/2016/11/06/first-period-houses-of-salem-massachusetts/</ref>\n|-\n| Watson Freeman House\t\t\n|\n| [[Sandwich, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1650<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| possibly demolished<ref>CAPE COD CANAL TRANSPORTATION STUDY pg. A94 https://www.mass.gov/files/documents/2019/10/21/CCTSAppendices19.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Bickman House\t\t\n|\n| [[Weymouth, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1650<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| located at 84 Sea Street. Right side of building is the oldest house in Weymouth<ref>https://www.weymouth.ma.us/sites/weymouthma/files/uploads/homes.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| John Harding House\t\t\n|\n| [[Medfield, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1651<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| 74 Harding St. from the timbers of the old garrison, used as protection during the Indian attacks <ref>DeSorgher: It's All in the Name; Who is Your Street Named After? https://patch.com/massachusetts/medfield/desorgher-it-s-all-in-the-name-who-is-your-street-named-after</ref>\n|-\n|  [[Goodspeed House]]\t\t\n| [[File:Goodspeed_House,_Marstons_Mills_MA.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Barnstable, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1653<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| \n|-\n|  John Chenery House\t\t\n| [[File:John Chenery House - Belmont, MA - DSC05303.JPG|100px]]\n| [[Belmont, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1654<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| 52 Washington Street<ref>https://www.belmont-ma.gov/sites/belmontma/files/u151/52_washington.pdf</ref>\n|-\n|  Retire Beckett House\t\t\n| [[File:Retire Beckett House.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Salem, Massachusetts]]\n| c. 1655<ref name=\"firstperiodnewengland.wordpress.com\"/>\n| Currently serves as the museum store at the [[House of Seven Gables]] after being moved to that location.<ref>https://7gables.org/history/the-retire-beckett-house/</ref>\n|-\n|  Keyes House\t\t\n| [[File:Keyes House at 16 Frances Hill Road in Westford MA Massachusetts built circa 1656.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Westford,